title: For Sale/Trade:  Nikon Monarch 3-9x40mm

postcontent: This is an older Nikon scope but in really good condition other than some ring marks from mounting. No scratches on the glass and it's as clear as any scope you'll look through that's $500 or less. This is an upper end Nikon that has a one piece tube and built in Japan. Notice on the lower end Nikon scopes that the turret housing in the middle of the scope has one side that is threaded into that housing, these are two piece tubes which aren't quiet as durable and allow another point for the nitrogen or argon purge gases to escape which leads to a cloudy scope. Notice also that the lower end Nikons like the Prostaff and Buckmasters are made in the Philippines.  This scope has a fine duplex cross hair reticle and is a 1" tube. I have some leupold STD mounting bases and rings available for sell as well if interested. The bases are two piece windage adjustable mounts that work on Remington 700. If interested I can mount and bore sight the scope for no additional charge and if time permits can dial it in with your rounds at your specified range.
